Name: Young Sheldon
Overview: Follow the misadventures of child prodigy Sheldon Cooper (first seen as an adult in "The Big Bang Theory") navigating the complexities of family, school, and social life in East Texas, showcasing his extraordinary intellect and the humorous challenges of being distinctly different.

Name: Beirut to Bosnia
Overview: Why have so many Muslims come to hate the West? In this controversial three-part series filmed in Lebanon, Gaza, Israel, Egypt, and Bosnia, Robert Fisk—award-winning Middle East and Balkans correspondent for the London Independent—reports on Muslim unrest as ideology, religion, history, and geography come into conflict. Contains strong imagery. Not available in French-speaking Canada. A Discovery Channel Production. 3-part series, 52 minutes each.

Name: SAS Rogue Heroes
Overview: Who dares wins. The adrenaline-fuelled origins of the fearless, reckless Special Forces unit, its legend forged among the mayhem of WWII.

Name: Ozark Law
Overview: “Ozark Law” joins the Lake Ozark Police Department and Osage Beach Police Department on their daily patrols, witnessing firsthand the challenges they face in maintaining order and ensuring safety in this lively midwestern destination.

Name: Letterkenny
Overview: The residents of Letterkenny belong to one of three groups: Hicks, Skids, and Hockey Players. The three groups are constantly feuding with each other over seemingly trivial matters; often ending with someone getting their ass kicked.

Name: Italy Unpacked
Overview: British art historian Andrew Graham-Dixon and Italian chef Giorgio Locatelli explore the varied regions of Italy and share their knowledge of the country's culture and cuisine. ‘Italy Unpacked’ follows on from the BBC’s successful series ‘Sicily Unpacked’ that aired in 2012.

Name: The Beauty
Overview: Modern society is obsessed with outward beauty. What if there was a way to guarantee you could become more and more beautiful every day? What if it was a sexually transmitted disease? In the world of The Beauty, physical perfection is attainable. The vast majority of the population has taken advantage of it, but Detectives Foster and Vaughn will soon discover it comes at a terrible price.
